00:19:16,067 --> 00:19:18,988
when you create a match of more than five or six, for example,

338
00:19:19,408 --> 00:19:22,269
you create this thing, the color converter.

339
00:19:23,289 --> 00:19:28,233
So in turn two, you actually activate the color converter with the green one, and this

340
00:19:28,273 --> 00:19:30,875
colors all the candies of another color to become green.

341
00:19:31,456 --> 00:19:36,841
In this case, what happens here is that all the orange candies become green, and a series

342
00:19:36,901 --> 00:19:40,344
of matches and cascades, and then this becomes the board state after that, which creates

343
00:19:40,364 --> 00:19:42,065
a new power-up for you, which is the chocolate bomb.

344
00:19:43,447 --> 00:19:46,109
And then when the player, in the third turn, when the player activates the chocolate bomb...

345
00:19:46,731 --> 00:19:50,163
it clears all the green again and it opens up new possibilities.

346
00:19:50,825 --> 00:19:53,574
And you can see that what happens here in the fourth or the fifth turn is that...

347
00:19:54,251 --> 00:19:58,774
The player can now move on, like many power-ups on the board, and the player can choose how

348
00:19:58,814 --> 00:20:02,856
he wants to engage the board at this point, whether he wants to go for the fish first,

349
00:20:02,876 --> 00:20:06,459
whether he wants to go for the striped candy, or whether he wants to match the chocolate

350
00:20:06,479 --> 00:20:06,699
bomb.

351
00:20:07,419 --> 00:20:13,523
The idea is that it starts from a linear one possible move, and it opens up slowly, so

352
00:20:13,563 --> 00:20:17,045
the players are guided slowly along by this invisible hand that we're talking about.

353
00:20:19,155 --> 00:20:21,296
The main idea is that you want to move the players forward.

354
00:20:21,336 --> 00:20:25,558
You want to give them choice, or at least some illusion of choice, that they have something

355
00:20:25,578 --> 00:20:26,599
that they can do in the game.

356
00:20:26,679 --> 00:20:30,060
But the main thing is that you're still trying to push them forward as much as you can.

357
00:20:32,461 --> 00:20:35,883
How we do this in our game, one example, is coming back to this level.

